TITLE: Processing GraphQL Documents in Code Generator Plugin (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This plugin snippet demonstrates how to iterate over the `documents` array, which contains details about parsed GraphQL files. For each document, it accesses its file `location` and the `document.definitions` (AST nodes) to extract operation names, then formats a string showing the file and its operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dotansimha/graphql-code-generator/blob/master/website/src/pages/docs/custom-codegen/plugin-structure.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
  plugin(schema, documents, config, info) {
    return documents
      .map(doc => {
        const docsNames = doc.document.definitions.map(def => def.name.value);

        return `File ${doc.location} contains: ${docsNames.join(', ')}`;
      })
      .join('\n');
  }
}
```

