TITLE: Removing Directives from GraphQL Documents (JS)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code illustrates how to remove a specific directive (in this case, `@localOnlyDirective`) from GraphQL documents using the `visit` function from the `graphql` library. It defines a CodegenConfig object and a documentTransforms function that iterates through each document and uses `visit` to remove nodes matching the directive name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dotansimha/graphql-code-generator/blob/master/packages/graphql-codegen-core/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import type { CodegenConfig } from '@graphql-codegen/cli';
import { visit } from 'graphql';

const config: CodegenConfig = {
  schema: 'https://localhost:4000/graphql',
  documents: ['src/**/*.tsx'],
  generates: {
    './src/gql/': {
      preset: 'client',
      documentTransforms: [
        {
          transform: ({ documents }) => {
            return documents.map(documentFile => {
              documentFile.document = visit(documentFile.document, {
                Directive: {
                  leave(node) {
                    if (node.name.value === 'localOnlyDirective') return null;
                  },
                },
              });
              return documentFile;
            });
          },
        },
      ],
    },
  },
};
export default config;
```

