TITLE: Modeling Unions with @union Directive in GraphQL - GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the @union directive to describe a GraphQL union with a discriminator field for MongoDB model output. Each type in the union is marked as an entity. Inputs: Types and union definitions. Limitations: Discriminator field is required. Outputs: Used to generate a TypeScript union with tagging.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dotansimha/graphql-code-generator/blob/master/website/src/pages/plugins/typescript/typescript-mongodb.mdx#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: GraphQL
CODE:
```
type A @entity {
  fieldA: String @column
}

type B @entity {
  fieldB: String @column
}

union PossibleType @union(discriminatorField: "entityType") = A | B
```

