TITLE: Validation Function to Enforce Configuration Constraints in GraphQL Plugin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates an enhanced plugin object including a `validate` function that checks for the presence of a required `mustHave` property in the plugin's configuration object. If validation fails, it throws an Error, ensuring correct plugin setup before execution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dotansimha/graphql-code-generator/blob/master/website/src/pages/docs/custom-codegen/validate-configuration.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
  plugin(schema, documents, config, info) {
    const typesMap = schema.getTypeMap()

    return Object.keys(typesMap).join('\n')
  },
  validate(schema, documents, config, outputFile, allPlugins) {
    if (!config.mustHave) {
      throw new Error(`You must specify "mustHave" in my plugin configuration!`)
    }
  }
}
```

